comments.text:
Palin is certainly not the brightest and I agree that people so ignorant 
being put into positions of power is destructive. However, in this video, 
she didn't say anything really dumb even though you can tell she was 
uncomfortable. Uygur is making an unfair criticism which can actually be 
challenged by smart conservative rhetoric. He is making it seem as if 
whatever Palin is saying is so obviously dumb but this is not the case. On 
the Israel and Palestinian issue, she said she's in favor of building more 
settlement which is the view of a number of conservatives in the US. I'm 
sure you can even find a number of Democrats to agree to that. What about 
the peace process becoming impossible because of it? Well, they are just 
being hypocritical about it, but not dumb. On the economy, it's just pure 
rhetoric. If she wasa in debate setting, she would be put to shame for her 
ignorance. But this is an interview and she didn't get a chance to say 
something that dumb and got away with it. About Afghanistan, the supposed 
contradiction is that she advocates more troops so the Afghanis can stand 
on their own without the help of troops. Well, she might be saying more 
troops now for the Afghanis now to defeat the enemy, so the Afghanis can be 
independent further down the road. My point? If you want to pick on Palin, 
there are a lot of ignorant things she said out there. But please do not 
try to find new things to pick on when there isn't, at least not in terms 
of them being so dumb! Let us remain constructive in our criticism!﻿
